documentContent: Machine learning models require large datasets for training. Neural networks use backpropagation to learn patterns from data.
Cloud computing provides scalable infrastructure on demand. AWS, Azure, and GCP are the major cloud providers in the market.
TypeScript is a typed superset of JavaScript that compiles to plain JavaScript. It adds static type checking to catch errors early.
Kubernetes orchestrates containerized applications across clusters. It automates deployment, scaling, and management of containers.
React is a JavaScript library for building user interfaces. It uses a virtual DOM for efficient rendering and component reusability.
PostgreSQL is a powerful open-source relational database. It supports advanced features like JSONB, full-text search, and window functions.
GraphQL is a query language for APIs. It allows clients to request exactly the data they need, avoiding over-fetching.
Docker containers package applications with their dependencies. They provide consistent environments across development and production.
Python is widely used for data science and machine learning. Libraries like NumPy, Pandas, and Scikit-learn make it powerful.
Redis is an in-memory data store used for caching and session management. It supports various data structures like strings, hashes, and sets.
REST APIs use HTTP methods for CRUD operations. They follow stateless principles and use standard HTTP status codes.
MongoDB is a NoSQL document database. It stores data in flexible JSON-like documents and scales horizontally.
Git is a distributed version control system. It enables collaboration through branches, merges, and remote repositories.
Microservices architecture breaks applications into small, independent services. Each service handles a specific business capability.
CI/CD pipelines automate software delivery. They include stages for build, test, and deployment to production.
TensorFlow is an open-source machine learning framework. It provides tools for building and training neural networks at scale.
JWT tokens authenticate users in stateless APIs. They contain encoded claims that can be verified without database lookups.
Elasticsearch is a distributed search and analytics engine. It provides full-text search capabilities with near real-time performance.
Vue.js is a progressive JavaScript framework. It features a reactive data binding system and component-based architecture.
Apache Kafka is a distributed streaming platform. It handles high-throughput message queues with fault tolerance and durability.
